        "Minor in Statistics": [
            "Minor in Statistics Statistical skills are in high demand across a wide range of disciplines, with job opportunities in nearly every field. The minor in statistics is designed to enhance a wide variety of undergraduate majors by providing valuable training in data analysis, and statistical modeling and inference. Students completing a minor in Statistics will demonstrate knowledge and understanding of statistical techniques and methodologies, working with real data, and performing data analysis. Students must successfully complete the requirements as listed in the program guide."
